Coronavirus disease data analysis Worlwide

Ongoing data science pipeline to process, analyse and visualise COVID-19 pandemia data.

corona_artwork.jpg

The current outbreak of coronavirus disease (COVID-19) that was first reported from Wuhan, China, on 31 December 2019.

Since mid-february, Johns Hopkins CSSE reports the number of diagnoses with the coronavirus and their residence on a daily base. The data contains the total number of positively tested (confirmed), deaths and recovery patients. ~The raw dataset can be found on the github repository. This dataset is daily updated.

This is a developing story :exclamation: Daily updates :exclamation:

Datasets:

  • :page_facing_up: Confirmed
  • :page_facing_up: Recovered
  • :page_facing_up: Deaths

Tips for improvements

Suggest on this project is appreciated. I am looking for new features for the data pipelines.

See data science pipeline /.github/src for technical details regarding data collection and cleaning.

:chart_with_upwards_trend: Graphs globally

The following graphs show the development of Coronavirus on a daily basis. The graphs are updated on an hourly basis and were generated automatically. Please validate the numbers in the graphs before publishing. See the license section for information about sharing the graphs.

Regression

The first predictions are based on exponential growth model.

Note, however that the data no longer behave exponentially. If we plot them on a log axis they deviate from the line quite drastically!
